<item>
            <title>[FLINK-4800] Introduce the TimestampedFileInputSplit for Continuous File Processing</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-4800</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Introduce the TimestampedFileInputSplit which extends the class FileInputSplit and also contains:&lt;br/&gt;
i) the modification time of the file the split belongs to and also, and&lt;br/&gt;
ii) when checkpointing, the point the reader is currently reading from.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The latter will be useful for rescaling. With this addition, the ContinuousFileMonitoringFunction sends TimestampedFileInputSplits &lt;br/&gt;
to the Readers, and the Readers&apos; state now contain only TimestampedFileInputSplits.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
